Now if you can understand that, it leads to this.  The warriors and mellee were &quot;balanced&quot; against each other, but in that balancing and with the kind of items dropping in the &quot;high&quot; end game they are balanced to the high end game and where it is leading. Once again the game is evolving ( life beyond level 60). Now, pre- Kunark, for those of you who have not been in this game for the total life of it, all the classes went through a balancing act and in the end it worked relatively well. With the release of Kunark things started to fall apart a bit. Adjustments were started but then more expansions to where we are today. In this process the druid has fallen so far behind it is unbelievable. Except for mellee skills, the druid was second in most casting classes, not all, and was a true all around &quot;jack of all trade&quot;. We are now &quot;jack of nothing&quot; really we have fallen so far behind. Casters to, have fallen behind in a number of areas also, as to where the high end game has gone and is going. Casters are getting &quot;balanced&quot;. This is level 60 balancing to the high end game. All balancing is relative to the warrior as they are the focal point of the game for Verant. If they get truely balanced compared to the way the warrior is, they should do quite well. The druid has been historically left behind by Verant through it's life in the game. The loot tables are puny for druids as compared to all the other classes and most &quot;uber&quot; loot that a druid can use, so can a shaman and cleric... in a power building guild the &quot;guild&quot; need always comes before the personal need and seldom does the druid get to aquire said loots before other classes are equiped. Why? because we cannot contribute as much to the raids as the others can.  We used to be able to be a very useful class but the game has evolved ( there is that word again) far past us. If it takes better dots,nukes heals, and/or buffs to put us back in our place then so be it. <br>
<br>
There will always be some of you that whine - that is to powerful to so and so - that is to much healing - your dots are to big - blah blah blah.  BUT this is NOT about pre-60 game anymore. As a Druid I want to catch up in my abilities relative to the raiding I am doing now and be usefull again.<br>
<br>
And I will say it again for those of you who have not been on boss raids but know so well that druids don't need such-and-such cause it is unbalancing to the game. Old norrath Vox ,Nagafen etc .. druids ok .. Kunark release druids fall behind a bit but new spells and stuff still make druid viable to the tougher boss mobs...Velious and then Luclin came out and a lot of ground lost for druids as other classes gained some improvement. We did finally gain  some better armor as in quest armor, or similar armor to it that drops in Umbral Plains but over all the new boss mobs drove us to the bottom of the class usability scale. If you have been on these &quot;uber&quot; raids you know that druid damage now is nothing whether dot or nuke, healing is meaningless against cleric CH and most other caster classes have one or more better versions of our buffs. Even as a secondary anything we suck bad now. For those that don't know these mobs in the &quot;end&quot; game hit for 600-1200 quads,rampage, summon, have rather high MR and have MEGA HP. 500K, 800K, 1mil HP.  They can have AoE dots that do 10k damage. They make Vox and Nagefen look old and crippled. The game has advanced and the druid really hasn't. So screw this crap about pre60 non raid balance. It is a relative thing. Have the uber 60equiped mellee hurt the &quot;balance&quot;? Not to bloody  much.  <br>
<br>
And what happens when Planes of Power expansion is released?<br>
